      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That’s a great question! Concrete is excellent at handling compressive forces, but it isn't as strong when it comes to tension. Steel rebar (reinforcement) is added to concrete to complement its weaknesses. The tensile strength of steel rebar helps the concrete handle both compression and tension, resulting in a much stronger and more durable foundation. This composite material leverages the strengths of both steel and concrete to create a robust structure.",
